DateTime-TimeAgo

DateTime::TimeAgo inspired by timeAgo jQuery plugin.
http://timeago.yarp.com/

Converts time intervals to human-friendly fuzzy English strings.

Pure-perl, simple procedural interface.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	./Build
	./Build test
	./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc DateTime::TimeAgo

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=DateTime-TimeAgo

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/DateTime-TimeAgo

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/DateTime-TimeAgo

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/DateTime-TimeAgo/


